    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how much pain you're in right now, and I want to tell you that your feelings are valid, but they don't define your worth as a parent. It sounds like you're carrying a heavy load, and sometimes when we're overwhelmed, we feel like we're dragging everyone down with us. But remember, even the most successful and capable people in the world have had days where they felt like a failure.\n\nYou mentioned your kids deserve better, and I think what they truly deserve is a parent who is honest about their struggles while still showing up for them. You don't have to be perfect to be a good parent; you just have to be present and willing to learn.\n\nIf you're feeling like you're dragging them down, maybe try reaching out to a counselor or a support group. Sometimes talking to someone who understands can help lighten the load. And if you're feeling like you need a break, that's okay too. You can't pour from an empty cup, and taking care of yourself is important for your kids' well-being.\n\nYou're not alone in this, and there are people who want to help you through this tough time. You've got this, and your kids are lucky to have you",
